# Approach 1: no extra stack
**NB: This approach is not recommended. It's just for fun.**

If we are willing to rewrite the input we can solve this problem w/o extra memory, because we can use the beginning of the string as a "stack".

```cpp
    static bool isValid(string& s) {
        char* p = s.data();
        for (char ch : s) {
            switch (ch) {
                case '(':
                    *p++ = ')';
                    break;
                case '[':
                    *p++ = ']';
                    break;
                case '{':
                    *p++ = '}';
                    break;
                default:
                    if (p == s.data()) return false;

                    if (*--p != ch) return false;
                    break;
            }
        }
        return p == s.data();
    }
```

